<sect2>
<title>Introduction to <application>Ghostscript</application></title>

<para><application>Ghostscript</application> is a versatile processor for Postscript data with
the ability to render Postscript to different targets. ESP Ghostscript
is a customized version of <acronym>GNU</acronym> Ghostscript that includes an enhanced
autoconf-based configuration script, the <acronym>CUPS</acronym> raster driver to support
<acronym>CUPS</acronym> raster printer drivers, and additional patches and drivers from
various Linux distributors.</para>

